TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit <Sensor> data collected during the descent phases (from surface to the parking depth and from the parking depth to the profile depth).

TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of Iridium packets used to transmit <Sensor> data collected during the drift at park depth.

TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Descent, nb points zone 1
TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of samples acquired by <Sensor> in the depth zone #<Z> during the descent phases (from surface to the parking depth and from the parking depth to the profile depth). Depth zone number: <Z> = 1..5

TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Nb points in drift
TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Park  measurements - Internal counter

TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Ascent, nb points zone 1
TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Number of samples acquired by <Sensor> in the depth zone #<Z> during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface. Depth zone number: <Z> = 1..5

TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: "X" type status sensor (1: normal, 0 if problem)
TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: The <Sensor> is OK (Yes/No).

TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Pressure offset (surface)
TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Surface pressure measured just before the float dives which is then used to correct pressure on board the float for the next profile.  Note: this is a relative offset. Autocorrected.

TECH_PARAM_MSG_LABEL: Pressure "subsurface"
TECH_PARAM_DESCRIPTION: Last (shallowest) pumped raw pressure sample acquired during the ascent from the profile depth to the surface (i.e. just before the cut-off pressure where the pump is stopped) (in dbars).
